Hamming Window Graph¶

In [50]:
from scipy import signal
from scipy.fftpack import fft, fftshift
window = signal.hamming(int(FL))
plt.plot(window)
plt.title("Hamming window of Frame Length")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")

Conclusion:¶

From this experiment we recorded a speech file of 2 sec with sampling frequency of 8kHz and plot it. then framed the recorded speech with frame length of 10 and 20 ms without and with overlap and calculated the frame length and the number of frames. In this we also considered 2 cases of overlap of 25%and 50% and lastly applied Hamming window on speech frames and analyse the frames
